LIMPOPO
cops seek help in finding a 56-year-old woman who went missing.  Police spokesperson constable Maphure Manamela said according to the victim's
son who reported the matter to the police, his mother was last seen
on Wednesday around 16:00 in Polokokwane. The son said, she was reportedly wearing a yellow blouse and cream white round
neck jersey. “She
had a black afro wig on, with a white and black hat at the time of her
disappearance,” Manamela said. Manamela said anyone with information that can assist the police in locating Rosina
is requested to contact Warrant officer Lesiba Mogale on 0799207419 or call the
police emergency number 0860010111. 